transcripts.text: Thank you, veterans.  Thank you for quiet mornings, family breakfasts, morning walks, and safe streets.  For builders, both of cities and of homes.  Thank you for realists, ordinary optimists, coffee shop companies, and boardroom companies.  For freedoms.  Choices.  Beliefs.  Thank you for your oath.  Thank you for 2 a.m.  night watches.  5 a.m.  rock watches.  Scrubbing.  Mobbing.  Plunging.  For papers.  Plans.  Routes.  For six-hour convoys.  Six-month deployments.  Thank you.  for following orders, leading your team, and carrying your brothers back home.  Thank you, veterans, for sticking to your oath so that we all can wake up to another quiet morning tomorrow.
